  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT32-kilavi">piṉṉiṉṟāṉ kūṟukiṉṟatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">Told by HIM who had entreated [her/the confidante].</p>
          </div>



        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT32">
<l>                kālaiyum pakaluṅ kaiyaṟu mālaiyu</l>
<l>                mūrtuñ ciyāmamum viṭiyalu meṉṟip</l>
<l>                poḻutiṭai teriyiṟ poyyē kāma</l>
<l>                māveṉa maṭaloṭu maṟukiṟ ṟōṉṟit</l>
<l>                teṟṟeṉat tūṟṟalum paḻiyē</l>
<l>                vāḻtalum paḻiyē pirivutalai variṉē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
               <l>Morning and midday and motionless evening</l>
               <l>and midnight when the village sleeps and dawn</l>
               <l rend="indent">if [still] familiar with these daytimes,</l>
               <l rend="indent4">desire [is but] a lie.<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">poyyē kāmam</term>: the antepositioned predicate noun <term xml:lang="ta">poy</term> is marked as such by <term xml:lang="ta">-ē</term>; the sentence remains open-ended.</note></l>
               <l rend="indent">As horse the Palmyra-stem, appearing in the streets</l>
               <l>blame in spreading [it] clearly,</l>
               <l>and blame in living,</l>
               <l rend="indent2">if separation comes to pass.</l>
                
                </lg>
        </div>
